THE ROMAN ORDO FOR THE THREE DAYS BEFORE EASTER.

The celebrated manuscript of Einsiedlen (Einsiedl. 326) contains, among other things, a fragment of the Ordo Romanus dealing with the last three days of Holy Week. The description given therein of the cere- monies differs in certain respects from that found in other texts. I reproduce it here according to the edition of J. B. de Rossi in vol. ii. of his Inscriptiones Christianae Urbis Romae, Part L, p. 34.
